<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue/1_1_2_OtherConstructedArea> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "identical to EAGLE class: 1112_OtherConstructions - Includes: e.g. asphalt, concrete, pave dings like on roads, parking lots, squares, storages areas, airport run ways, quays, sealed bottom pools, unvegetated cemeteries. - Excludes: gravel bed of railway track. It is an artificial surface but not impervious, better to be placed under Gravel, Pebble"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue/1_1_1_Building> <http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue/2_5_12_Herbaceous> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This large class contains all kind of arable crops, pastures, meadows and natural grasslands. As for bare soil it is in the context of agricultural use not essential to assign the object the correct class, as the class of an object is a rather random issue depending on the acquisition date. However it is important to differentiate objects of the same class, if they are located next to each other, and if they can differentiate according to their vegetation index and physiognomic appearance."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "INSPIRE extensibility: open, internal by value"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/LISALandCoverClassValue:1> .
